[Yeo Jun-wan]

119
00:08:47,330 --> 00:08:48,650
[Get me the company files.]

120
00:08:49,180 --> 00:08:51,780
[I'm sure you heard,
but Father declined my request.]

121
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:59,780
[Yeo Jun-wan]

122
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:54,110
[I'm not asking as your family.]

123
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:56,220
[I don't have one anyway.]

124
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:00,530
[You pay my credit card bills]

125
00:08:59,870 --> 00:09:07,530
[Yeo Jun-wan]

126
00:09:02,290 --> 00:09:03,960
[to buy me out of this family.]

127
00:09:05,150 --> 00:09:06,520
[Consider this as an advance.]

128
00:09:24,510 --> 00:09:26,710
Jun, where are you headed?
Let's grab something to eat.

129
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:28,120
Hi.

130
00:09:28,210 --> 00:09:29,750
-Hello.
-Jun!

131
00:09:30,010 --> 00:09:32,340
Next time.
I'll hear your answer next time.

132
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:34,940
I'm scared.

133
00:09:35,030 --> 00:09:36,660
-Let's go!
-Sure.

134
00:09:36,740 --> 00:09:38,020
One, two, three!

135
00:09:38,110 --> 00:09:40,840
-I should at least give him an answer.
-Jun, one more.

136
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:42,200
One, two, three.

137
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:45,500
Gosh, you look amazing!

138
00:09:46,030 --> 00:09:48,050
-Do you like tteokbokki?
-One, two, three.

139
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:49,330
Take the shot.

140
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:52,010
Let's go for some tteokbokki.

141
00:09:52,140 --> 00:09:54,170
-What do you say?
-Let's go.

142
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:58,570
[He told me about ten things
I should remember.]

143
00:09:59,180 --> 00:10:01,650
[I have a good memory,
so let me demonstrate.]

144
00:10:03,190 --> 00:10:07,150
[One, don’t demand her to be girly.]

145
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,660
Two, don't...

146
00:10:09,740 --> 00:10:13,260
Two, don’t let her drink
more than three shots.

147
00:10:13,660 --> 00:10:15,020
She hits random people, you see.

148
00:10:16,610 --> 00:10:20,260
[Don't order coke or juice at a cafe]

149
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,620
[and order coffee.]

150
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:24,220
When she hits you,

151
00:10:24,310 --> 00:10:26,600
pretend that it hurts when it doesn’t

152
00:10:26,990 --> 00:10:28,970
[and bear the pain when it does.]

153
00:10:29,540 --> 00:10:31,170
[If she complains about her sore feet,]

154
00:10:31,610 --> 00:10:33,460
[swap shoes with her.]

155
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:39,440
[She likes to write...]

156
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:54,930
Yeo Jun,

157
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,350
let's talk in private.

158
00:11:02,460 --> 00:11:08,220
[Myungil University]

159
00:11:15,350 --> 00:11:16,490
What's this about?

160
00:11:16,980 --> 00:11:19,220
I won't stop or repeat myself,
so listen carefully.

161
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:23,000
My So-bin has acrophobia, agoraphobia,
and is scared of cockroaches.

162
00:11:23,090 --> 00:11:24,810
She's scared of just about anything.

163
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:26,350
She also likes mint chocolate flavor.

164
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:28,060
Pineapples on pizza? Loves them.

165
00:11:28,150 --> 00:11:29,780
But she hates the crust,
so eat it instead.

166
00:11:29,870 --> 00:11:31,720
When eating sundae,
she only enjoys the liver.

167
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:32,860
With tteokbokki, she likes

168
00:11:32,950 --> 00:11:34,750
cheap fish cakes with
flour-based rice cakes.

169
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:35,850
Spicy food? Loves them.

170
00:11:35,940 --> 00:11:37,440
She drinks to enjoy hangover dishes.

171
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:39,330
Tteokbokki, sundaeguk,
gamjatang, yukgaejang...

172
00:11:39,420 --> 00:11:40,380
Wait. With maratang,

173
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:42,980
she goes for a mid-spicy level
with dried tofu and napa cabbage.

174
00:11:43,070 --> 00:11:44,870
Did you get all that?
Did you listen carefully?

175
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:55,210
You'll ace the test on Kim So-bin.

176
00:11:55,610 --> 00:11:57,630
Yes, I even wrote a thesis on her.

177
00:11:57,720 --> 00:12:00,540
And? So what if you know a lot about her?

178
00:12:00,620 --> 00:12:03,090
So what if you're old friends? Who cares?

179
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:06,040
-My So-bin--
-Stop calling her that.

180
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:07,880
I call her that because she's my So-bin,

181
00:12:07,970 --> 00:12:09,250
not your So-bin.

182
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:11,320
I still haven't approved
your relationship.

183
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,380
If something stirs inside me

184
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:14,880
that makes me approve,

185
00:12:16,420 --> 00:12:18,000
then I'll call her your So-bin.

186
00:12:22,140 --> 00:12:24,470
Fine, she can be yours.

187
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:25,970
Right. What?

188
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:28,120
She'll be "honey" and "sweetie" to me.

189
00:12:28,610 --> 00:12:31,070
Honey? Sweetie?

190
00:12:31,950 --> 00:12:33,090
Gosh, are you insane?

191
00:12:33,180 --> 00:12:35,340
Why can't I call my girlfriend that?

192
00:12:35,820 --> 00:12:36,880
Why can't I?

193
00:12:37,890 --> 00:12:41,410
Well, it's just that
I have a lot to tell you about her.

194
00:12:43,130 --> 00:12:44,360
So why don't we

195
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:47,040
be good friends?

196
00:14:09,060 --> 00:14:10,160
Hand it over.

197
00:14:10,470 --> 00:14:12,580
It's proper manners to greet someone

198
00:14:12,670 --> 00:14:14,120
before addressing business.

199
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:16,850
How about a hug?

200
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:19,050
A bow?

201
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:21,990
Let's hear it.

202
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:22,920
[2020 Second-half Sales Report:
Mijin Foods]

203
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:25,560
What desperate reason
did you need this for

204
00:14:25,650 --> 00:14:27,540
that made you come to me for a favor?

205
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,750
And don't say it's for a school project.

206
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:35,770
It's for a friend.

207
00:14:38,410 --> 00:14:39,590
A friend?

208
00:14:40,610 --> 00:14:43,510
I promised to get this material.

209
00:14:44,870 --> 00:14:46,280
You've got yourself a friend?

210
00:14:46,810 --> 00:14:48,610
What's it to you anyway?

211
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:55,430
I mentioned this on the phone,

212
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:57,020
but the family is gathering next week.

213
00:14:58,030 --> 00:15:00,580
Don't come.
No one's waiting for you anyway.

214
00:15:03,880 --> 00:15:07,140
I had my DNA tested. Did you know that?

215
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:11,190
Because I thought my parents
weren't my parents?

216
00:15:11,670 --> 00:15:12,770
No.

217
00:15:13,870 --> 00:15:15,590
Because there's no chance
you're my brother.

218
00:15:15,670 --> 00:15:17,700
Unfortunately,
you're my biological brother.

219
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:21,970
Give me your word if you want this file.

220
00:15:22,850 --> 00:15:24,300
-Don't come home.
-No.

221
00:15:25,660 --> 00:15:26,810
I'll be there.

222
00:15:27,380 --> 00:15:28,830
When do I ever listen to you anyway?

223
00:15:29,530 --> 00:15:30,990
Pay me all the money you want.

224
00:15:32,170 --> 00:15:33,450
I'll still be at the house.

225
00:16:03,060 --> 00:16:05,130
Did you meet the visitor
you were expecting?

226
00:16:06,410 --> 00:16:07,330
Yes.

227
00:16:07,420 --> 00:16:09,270
Then please hurry.
The uni president awaits you.

228
00:16:09,350 --> 00:16:10,540
I'll be right there.

229
00:16:10,890 --> 00:16:12,350
It must've been an important visitor

230
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:14,280
for you to push
your meeting with the president.

231
00:16:40,950 --> 00:16:42,130
Yeo Jun-wan and...

232
00:16:43,230 --> 00:16:44,380
Yeo Jun.

233
00:16:44,730 --> 00:16:46,230
What about you? Any siblings?

234
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:49,570
No, I'm an only child.

235
00:16:59,340 --> 00:17:01,270
Why didn't you say hi earlier?
You saw me, right?

236
00:17:03,030 --> 00:17:04,790
Well, you stand out wherever you go.

237
00:17:06,109 --> 00:17:09,060
Am I that blinding?
Do I shine bright like a diamond?

238
00:17:10,119 --> 00:17:12,230
That means you can find me anywhere.

239
00:17:13,859 --> 00:17:14,960
Right.

240
00:17:17,109 --> 00:17:18,569
I looked at you to say something.

241
00:17:20,550 --> 00:17:23,230
I'll answer what I didn't the other day.

242
00:17:23,540 --> 00:17:24,640
Just a second.

243
00:17:26,490 --> 00:17:27,630
Let me brace myself first.

244
00:17:32,340 --> 00:17:33,480
Go ahead.

245
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:36,610
Thank you for telling me
about how you feel.

246
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:38,980
But...

247
00:17:40,430 --> 00:17:41,840
I still stand by what I said

248
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:45,540
about not knowing you
and being scared of you.

249
00:17:47,870 --> 00:17:49,370
Do you want to get to know me, though?

250
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:55,390
You do.

251
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,100
A little.

252
00:18:00,890 --> 00:18:01,990
Well,

253
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:05,340
it's only because I'm a curious person.

254
00:18:06,260 --> 00:18:07,710
Not because I like you.

255
00:18:08,510 --> 00:18:09,910
Let me be clear with that.

256
00:18:11,630 --> 00:18:14,010
Why bother?
I'm good with it not being clear.

257
00:18:14,490 --> 00:18:17,000
Also, unresolved curiosity
will give you constipation.

258
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,000
Okay, fine.

259
00:18:21,710 --> 00:18:24,260
Every day, I'll let you know
something about me.

260
00:18:24,740 --> 00:18:27,730
Remember them as I list them,
but don't fall too hard for me.

261
00:18:28,570 --> 00:18:29,850
That'll never happen.

262
00:18:29,930 --> 00:18:32,710
I'm not like that anymore.
I'm a new person now.

263
00:18:33,450 --> 00:18:36,270
This is my declaration,
so don't you forget it.

264
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:39,530
Well, two negatives make a positive.

265
00:18:41,070 --> 00:18:44,590
Okay, fine. Fall for me slightly then,
although that's hard to do.

266
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:46,610
What about you?

267
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:50,040
Are you curious about me?

268
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:52,940
It was your first time
being open about your feelings.

269
00:18:54,130 --> 00:18:56,950
Why did I have to be your first, though?

270
00:18:59,630 --> 00:19:01,880
I'm not trying
to put a meaning to it, but--

271
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:04,340
Yes. I'm curious about you.

272
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:20,180
Either be formal with me or don't
for crying out loud.

273
00:19:20,270 --> 00:19:21,540
You're confusing me.

274
00:19:22,420 --> 00:19:24,450
I'd rather you be consistent.

275
00:19:25,020 --> 00:19:26,120
I'm off then.

276
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:29,730
Unbelievable. You just dug your own grave.

277
00:19:40,510 --> 00:19:47,810
[Nam Soo-hyun]

278
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:44,160
[You're not passed out
on the street, are you?]

279
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:46,540
[Get some rest at home.]

280
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:59,520
Nam Soo-hyun, seriously?
What if you pass out again?

281
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:10,820
Soo-hyun passed out?

282
00:20:26,580 --> 00:20:28,290
You really don't listen, do you?

283
00:20:28,780 --> 00:20:31,330
I can't believe you paid
a week's worth in advance.

284
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:33,310
As if I can spend a week lying down.

285
00:20:34,890 --> 00:20:37,360
What's wrong with using me
to take it easy for a week?

286
00:20:37,620 --> 00:20:39,860
Others are fine spending my gold card.

287
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:44,350
Anyway, take this.

288
00:20:45,230 --> 00:20:46,600
It's the material I promised.

289
00:20:48,930 --> 00:20:50,290
[2020 Second-half Sales Report:
Mijin Foods]

290
00:20:56,890 --> 00:20:57,990
Here.

291
00:21:00,370 --> 00:21:01,510
What's this?

292
00:21:03,270 --> 00:21:05,160
Did we agree on a payment?

293
00:21:05,340 --> 00:21:06,750
It's what I owe you.

294
00:21:09,340 --> 00:21:11,280
Did you work all night
in the state you're in?

295
00:21:13,390 --> 00:21:15,550
You got the money this fast?

296
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:17,130
Did you take out a loan?

297
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:19,160
Loans aren't issued to people like me.

298
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:20,700
Did you go to a loan shark then?

299
00:21:20,780 --> 00:21:23,340
Will you be buried alive

300
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:24,880
if you don't pay it back?

301
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,060
That's enough.

302
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:28,400
Then...

303
00:21:29,190 --> 00:21:32,050
it was so that I wouldn't have
a reason to be clingy.

304
00:21:33,980 --> 00:21:35,170
Did you sell your organs?

305
00:21:36,710 --> 00:21:38,870
Let me see if you still have them all.

306
00:21:39,350 --> 00:21:40,540
Why won't you look at me?

307
00:21:41,020 --> 00:21:42,430
Don't tell me you sold an eye.

308
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:46,040
Six day's worth of hospital stay
was canceled on your credit card.

309
00:21:46,130 --> 00:21:47,400
You can check.

310
00:21:47,580 --> 00:21:49,210
I now owe you nothing.

311
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:52,200
-But you do.
-What?

312
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,580
As if anyone would steal that.

313
00:22:03,070 --> 00:22:05,180
I gave the watch a secondhand price,

314
00:22:06,150 --> 00:22:08,440
but tell me the price
if it had a sentimental value.

315
00:22:08,610 --> 00:22:09,840
I didn't know of that.

316
00:22:12,620 --> 00:22:13,760
You owe me emotionally.

317
00:22:16,880 --> 00:22:20,620
How will you pay me back
for trampling on my heartfelt generosity?

318
00:22:22,910 --> 00:22:26,040
That was the price for being clingy.

319
00:22:29,380 --> 00:22:31,360
You still won't get rid of me, though.

320
00:22:31,670 --> 00:22:34,350
Don't you get cocky. You'll soon miss me!

321
00:22:34,840 --> 00:22:36,680
You'll want to see me!

322
00:22:46,850 --> 00:22:50,150
[Professor, thank you
for going over my dissertation.]

323
00:22:50,410 --> 00:22:53,670
[I won the participation award
all thanks to you.]

324
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:57,720
[You weren't at your office,
so I'm sending you a text instead.]

325
00:22:58,290 --> 00:22:59,870
[Check outside your door.]

326
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:11,310
[Kim So-bin]

327
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:31,460
Professor,

328
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:34,280
I'll head in for the day.

329
00:23:34,370 --> 00:23:35,860
Sure. Good job today.

330
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:38,810
-Have me back at any time.
-Sure.

331
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:41,540
Just a second.

332
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:45,680
What's this? I don't see a name.

333
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:49,860
Oh, it's mine.

334
00:23:51,570 --> 00:23:53,860
Please utilize it however you want.

335
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:58,170
You want me to cite this?

336
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:00,280
Do I seem like a joke to you?

337
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:03,630
I'm sorry, ma'am.

338
00:24:04,550 --> 00:24:05,650
You're dismissed.

339
00:24:07,410 --> 00:24:08,560
Yes, ma'am.

340
00:24:17,530 --> 00:24:19,120
Is she really dating Yeo Jun?

341
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,480
Jun must be insane.

342
00:24:24,350 --> 00:24:26,330
Hey, that's Yeo Jun's girlfriend.

343
00:24:34,650 --> 00:24:35,750
Hi.

344
00:24:44,060 --> 00:24:45,380
Hey, So-bin.

345
00:24:48,420 --> 00:24:51,100
I heard you're going out with Jun.
Is that true?

346
00:24:51,190 --> 00:24:53,790
What? Who said that?

347
00:24:54,270 --> 00:24:55,720
So it's true.

348
00:24:56,820 --> 00:24:58,010
Well--

349
00:24:58,100 --> 00:25:02,760
So-bin, you hit the jackpot.
Yeo Jun of all people?

350
00:25:03,420 --> 00:25:05,670
I hear that computer engineering student

351
00:25:05,750 --> 00:25:08,350
is also from a rich family
of a rural city.

352
00:25:08,440 --> 00:25:11,740
A fair face may hide a foul heart.

353
00:25:13,230 --> 00:25:15,080
That's a bit cruel coming from someone

354
00:25:15,610 --> 00:25:16,840
who doesn't have all the facts.

355
00:25:16,930 --> 00:25:19,040
I know. If only I had known.

356
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:22,960
I would've made a move on Jun sooner
had I known he'd date someone like you.

357
00:25:23,310 --> 00:25:27,010
You see, I thought he had high standards

358
00:25:27,090 --> 00:25:28,190
and was intimidated.

359
00:25:28,550 --> 00:25:31,360
My bad. We'll see how long you last.

360
00:25:32,150 --> 00:25:33,300
Let's go.

361
00:25:43,150 --> 00:25:44,520
Ta-da.

362
00:25:45,350 --> 00:25:47,640
Wait. Where did she go?

363
00:25:49,270 --> 00:25:51,470
I'm totally embodying Leon today.

364
00:25:52,750 --> 00:25:54,110
It's her loss.

365
00:26:03,090 --> 00:26:05,330
You should watch the world
from this side too.

366
00:26:05,900 --> 00:26:07,970
I'll show you off in a minute.

367
00:26:16,420 --> 00:26:18,000
I see she's finally done.

368
00:26:20,070 --> 00:26:23,410
[The Effects of Family Conflict
on Work Ability]

369
00:26:26,670 --> 00:26:28,300
Hey, you're here.

370
00:26:29,530 --> 00:26:31,690
You shouldn't be here
without my permission.

371
00:26:31,770 --> 00:26:33,930
You don't ask
before entering my office either.

372
00:26:34,370 --> 00:26:36,310
I know you steal my red ginseng candy
all the time.

373
00:26:36,390 --> 00:26:38,810
Whatever. Now, leave.

374
00:26:41,230 --> 00:26:42,510
I'm mistaken, right?

375
00:26:42,910 --> 00:26:44,010
Regarding what?

376
00:26:45,330 --> 00:26:46,600
And what on earth is that?

377
00:26:47,750 --> 00:26:49,070
That's from So-bin...

378
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:53,250
Looks like you've finished
your dissertation.

379
00:26:53,330 --> 00:26:55,670
Right. So? Are you asking me to a meal?

380
00:26:55,750 --> 00:26:56,810
No thanks.

381
00:26:58,920 --> 00:27:01,340
I saw that you copied
a student's dissertation.

382
00:27:01,430 --> 00:27:03,940
Yes, I took a line that wasn't so bad.

383
00:27:04,290 --> 00:27:05,610
What about it?

384
00:27:05,700 --> 00:27:08,780
Someone even took my work
and copied all of it.

385
00:27:08,870 --> 00:27:11,680
Darn that Professor Choi.

386
00:27:11,990 --> 00:27:13,400
Because of that Professor Choi,

387
00:27:13,490 --> 00:27:15,380
you took time off school
and fell off the grid.

388
00:27:15,770 --> 00:27:18,060
I look for you everywhere.

389
00:27:18,590 --> 00:27:22,590
That's how wronged you felt,
but here you are doing the same thing.

390
00:27:22,990 --> 00:27:24,270
Are you becoming Professor Choi?

391
00:27:25,230 --> 00:27:27,960
Or is this your way of payback

392
00:27:29,020 --> 00:27:30,210
to Kim So-bin?

393
00:27:31,830 --> 00:27:35,130
Kim So-bin?
Why would you mention her of all people?

394
00:27:36,370 --> 00:27:38,210
Because it's her work.

395
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:42,040
I went over it for her
although that only involved me reading it.

396
00:27:44,150 --> 00:27:46,090
Is that how low you think of me?

397
00:27:47,280 --> 00:27:51,850
Let's not cross the line, Soo-kyung.

398
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,140
Park Si-jae.

399
00:27:55,020 --> 00:27:57,570
I could say the same to you
and keep your mouth shut.

400
00:27:58,280 --> 00:27:59,420
Got it?

401
00:28:21,160 --> 00:28:22,350
So-bin!

402
00:28:26,350 --> 00:28:29,210
You called me first, so I came running.

403
00:28:29,300 --> 00:28:31,100
Did you tell the others

404
00:28:31,720 --> 00:28:33,130
that we're dating?

405
00:28:33,570 --> 00:28:35,150
I thought this was a secret relationship.

406
00:28:36,290 --> 00:28:39,150
If you want, we can go public.

407
00:28:40,250 --> 00:28:41,840
Only you and I know about this

408
00:28:42,670 --> 00:28:44,480
and Chan-ki wouldn't have spilled.

409
00:28:47,430 --> 00:28:48,660
That's a weird thing to say.

410
00:28:50,070 --> 00:28:51,870
You keep taking his side

411
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,380
and accusing me instead.

412
00:28:55,920 --> 00:28:57,990
Well, I mean--

413
00:28:58,070 --> 00:29:00,760
That's not love. It's a habit.

414
00:29:01,510 --> 00:29:03,090
Whether it's real between us or not,

415
00:29:03,970 --> 00:29:05,860
don't take his side in my presence.

416
00:29:08,550 --> 00:29:09,690
No matter what it is about,

417
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:14,530
I don't like being the center of gossip.

418
00:29:16,770 --> 00:29:18,970
-You may be used to it but--
-I don't like it either.

419
00:29:19,940 --> 00:29:21,310
Us dating...

420
00:29:23,330 --> 00:29:24,560
is a lie anyway.

421
00:29:28,300 --> 00:29:30,190
Hey, Jun. It's time for class!

422
00:29:41,500 --> 00:29:42,870
[Myungil University]

423
00:29:52,370 --> 00:29:54,350
-Here she comes.
-Is that her?

424
00:29:54,440 --> 00:29:56,240
She's Yeo Jun's girlfriend?

425
00:29:57,030 --> 00:29:58,660
Jun's way out of her league.

426
00:29:58,750 --> 00:30:00,770
Tell me about it. Unbelievable.

427
00:30:01,260 --> 00:30:03,850
-She's Jun's girlfriend.
-Talk about a mismatch.

428
00:30:03,940 --> 00:30:05,920
-I'd be more compatible.
-No, me.

429
00:30:09,310 --> 00:30:11,110
Yeo Jun has a girlfriend?

430
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:13,840
Yes, she flirted with him endlessly.

431
00:30:15,120 --> 00:30:18,680
[Myungil University]

432
00:30:20,530 --> 00:30:23,040
Her mom had an affair
and is leaving her family.

433
00:30:23,130 --> 00:30:24,840
No, her dad had an affair

434
00:30:24,930 --> 00:30:26,950
[and replaced her mom
with his girlfriend.]

435
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:28,850
[She has a half-sibling.]

436
00:30:28,980 --> 00:30:30,960
So-bin will be taken to an orphanage.

437
00:30:31,090 --> 00:30:34,390
-♫ She's an orphan ♫
-♫ She's an orphan ♫

438
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:37,780
-♫ She's an orphan ♫
-♫ She's an orphan ♫

439
00:30:37,870 --> 00:30:41,210
-♫ She's an orphan ♫
-♫ She's an orphan ♫

440
00:30:41,300 --> 00:30:44,600
-♫ She's an orphan ♫
-♫ She's an orphan ♫

441
00:30:44,690 --> 00:30:47,990
-♫ She's an orphan ♫
-♫ She's an orphan ♫

442
00:30:48,070 --> 00:30:51,420
-♫ She's an orphan ♫
-♫ She's an orphan ♫

443
00:31:12,270 --> 00:31:14,740
Just apologize to Soo-hyun and come back.

444
00:31:16,630 --> 00:31:19,580
"Apologize"?
You're telling me to apologize to him?

445
00:31:19,660 --> 00:31:21,600
Don't tell me you're siding with Soo-hyun.

446
00:31:21,950 --> 00:31:23,890
It's just Soo-hyun and So-bin.

447
00:31:23,980 --> 00:31:25,690
Side with us, and we outnumber them.

448
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:28,860
Jun, are you really going out with So-bin?

449
00:31:28,950 --> 00:31:30,530
Is that why you can't side with us?

450
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:34,800
I don't like being the center of gossip.

451
00:31:38,940 --> 00:31:40,390
No, it's not that.

452
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:42,980
I knew it. Why would you?

453
00:31:43,340 --> 00:31:46,550
This is why you shouldn't be too nice
to all sorts of losers.

454
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:49,360
"Losers"?

455
00:31:49,940 --> 00:31:51,830
-Are you one of them?
-What?

456
00:31:52,180 --> 00:31:55,040
Hey, Yeo Jun. That was so rude.

457
00:31:55,130 --> 00:31:56,360
I'm off.

458
00:31:56,140 --> 00:31:59,620
[Startup Project]

459
00:31:57,370 --> 00:31:59,440
Don't be so difficult. Just side with us!

460
00:31:59,700 --> 00:32:02,120
You won't get anywhere without us.

461
00:32:04,590 --> 00:32:06,610
Are you confident
that you can beat Soo-hyun?

462
00:32:07,270 --> 00:32:10,180
We'll be doomed if they do a better job.

463
00:32:12,510 --> 00:32:14,140
That won't happen if they can't present.

464
00:32:21,750 --> 00:32:23,070
This is Nam Soo-hyun's?

465
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:25,220
He dropped it.

466
00:32:27,780 --> 00:32:28,960
Look.

467
00:32:29,050 --> 00:32:30,680
[What I owe to Yeo Jun]

468
00:32:30,770 --> 00:32:32,530
[Total: 1.2 million won]

469
00:32:32,620 --> 00:32:35,170
I knew it. He figured out how nice Jun is

470
00:32:35,260 --> 00:32:36,840
and totally took advantage of him.

471
00:32:37,460 --> 00:32:38,780
He's like a leech.

472
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:40,980
Were they close behind our backs?

473
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:43,700
Jun should've come to us
and told us about this.

474
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:50,350
Where are you?

475
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:56,070
Hey.

476
00:32:59,370 --> 00:33:00,470
So-bin!

477
00:33:27,220 --> 00:33:28,850
Sorry, I'm sorry about that.

478
00:34:15,179 --> 00:34:16,280
So-bin!

479
00:34:19,100 --> 00:34:20,280
Are you all right?

480
00:34:24,900 --> 00:34:26,090
Don't touch me.

481
00:34:31,239 --> 00:34:32,429
Did something happen?

482
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:34,719
Did someone say something mean to you

483
00:34:34,800 --> 00:34:36,080
for dating me?

484
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:38,760
Can you leave me alone?
I want to be alone.

485
00:34:45,540 --> 00:34:47,780
What's wrong? Are you not feeling well?

486
00:34:48,270 --> 00:34:49,590
I don't want to talk about it.

487
00:34:50,780 --> 00:34:51,960
You won't get it anyway.

488
00:34:52,050 --> 00:34:53,770
That is up to me.

489
00:34:53,860 --> 00:34:55,090
You can at least tell me.

490
00:34:55,179 --> 00:34:56,889
I don't want to. Why should I?

491
00:35:04,940 --> 00:35:08,290
Has getting involved with me
made your life difficult?

492
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,500
Yes.

493
00:35:13,130 --> 00:35:14,270
That said,

494
00:35:16,430 --> 00:35:18,190
I don't want to have anything
to do with you.

495
00:35:22,980 --> 00:35:24,220
Do you really mean it?

496
00:35:25,620 --> 00:35:26,680
Yes.

497
00:35:29,580 --> 00:35:30,860
Yes.

498
00:35:32,090 --> 00:35:33,280
I'm curious about you.

499
00:35:39,220 --> 00:35:40,890
I'm not curious about you at all.

500
00:35:43,270 --> 00:35:44,630
So don't be curious about me.

501
00:35:47,980 --> 00:35:49,120
So you really mean it.

502
00:35:49,740 --> 00:35:51,630
We were fine
when we didn't know each other.

503
00:35:54,710 --> 00:35:56,340
Let's just go back to that.

504
00:36:18,950 --> 00:36:21,500
[You can't even stay out of trouble?]

505
00:36:22,340 --> 00:36:26,040
Don't ruin your brother's reputation!

506
00:36:27,750 --> 00:36:31,010
-I'm sorry, Mother.
-You're such a troublemaker.

507
00:36:32,680 --> 00:36:35,760
You make people around you so miserable.

508
00:36:36,510 --> 00:36:39,240
If you behave yourself,
we'll have no problems at all.

509
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:41,170
Live like you're dead.

510
00:36:41,260 --> 00:36:43,110
Don't create a roadblock for your brother!

511
00:37:07,350 --> 00:37:09,900
I won't repeat myself. Quit and leave.

512
00:37:10,920 --> 00:37:13,340
-Professor.
-I have nothing else to say to you.

513
00:37:13,950 --> 00:37:15,050
Get out.

514
00:37:33,530 --> 00:37:38,060
[Department of Business Administration,
Professor Song Soo-kyung]

515
00:37:38,150 --> 00:37:43,560
[Department of Business Administration,
Professor Song Soo-kyung]

516
00:38:08,640 --> 00:38:09,830
We meet again.

517
00:38:11,550 --> 00:38:13,750
This is where
the convenience store thug works.

518
00:38:14,710 --> 00:38:16,120
I guess that wasn't enough.

519
00:38:16,430 --> 00:38:18,720
My friends were afraid you'd actually die,

520
00:38:18,810 --> 00:38:20,170
so they went super easy on you.

521
00:38:23,870 --> 00:38:25,580
Hey, Jun.

522
00:38:26,770 --> 00:38:28,970
Did Nam Soo-hyun extort money from you?

523
00:38:30,110 --> 00:38:31,350
I see.

524
00:38:31,430 --> 00:38:33,150
I'm sure he's done it to other fools.

525
00:38:33,240 --> 00:38:34,340
Don't worry.

526
00:38:34,430 --> 00:38:37,200
We're collecting evidence
to help you get your revenge.

527
00:38:37,290 --> 00:38:39,400
That's right. Hurry over.

528
00:38:42,170 --> 00:38:43,450
Let's get some fresh air.

529
00:38:46,350 --> 00:38:47,930
Is she going to beat up someone else?

530
00:38:48,770 --> 00:38:50,270
What does she like about UP?

531
00:38:50,620 --> 00:38:52,070
How did he seduce her?

532
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:55,150
Poor losers like him are always fearless
because they're desperate.

533
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:56,950
They don't know
when not to cross the line.

534
00:38:57,170 --> 00:38:59,900
Guys, let's just drink.

535
00:39:02,590 --> 00:39:03,730
Cheers.

536
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:11,430
Hello.

537
00:39:20,230 --> 00:39:23,050
I'm sorry. I'll take care of their bill
and take them home.

538
00:39:23,660 --> 00:39:25,070
Why would you pay for their drinks?

539
00:39:26,520 --> 00:39:27,580
Sorry?

540
00:39:28,110 --> 00:39:30,750
I'll wake them up and deal with it.
Just go home.

541
00:39:30,920 --> 00:39:32,370
Aren't you Yeo Jun in first year?

542
00:39:32,680 --> 00:39:35,190
Yes, do you go to my school?

543
00:39:35,940 --> 00:39:37,570
I'm Wang Young-ran, a senior in PE major.

544
00:39:38,970 --> 00:39:41,530
Are you and Soo-hyun close?

545
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:44,250
No, we're not close.

546
00:39:44,830 --> 00:39:48,040
I want to befriend him, but it's hard.

547
00:39:50,110 --> 00:39:52,130
I just wanted to ask
if you've talked to him.

548
00:39:52,610 --> 00:39:54,950
Soo-hyun and I are friends,
but I can't get hold of him.

549
00:39:55,390 --> 00:39:57,100
You're Soo-hyun's friend?

550
00:39:57,450 --> 00:39:59,520
What did you do to become his friend?

551
00:39:59,920 --> 00:40:01,990
He wants to cut me off
whenever I try to do anything.

552
00:40:03,830 --> 00:40:05,020
He's a difficult one.

553
00:40:05,420 --> 00:40:08,060
But if I don't do anything,
he'll never even glance at me.

554
00:40:09,070 --> 00:40:10,130
Right?

555
00:40:10,650 --> 00:40:13,560
If I were asked to write just one line
on my resume,

556
00:40:13,870 --> 00:40:16,550
I'd write "Nam Soo-hyun's only friend."
Nothing else.

557
00:40:18,660 --> 00:40:20,030
That was an overshare, wasn't it?

558
00:40:21,870 --> 00:40:26,190
Then I'll be "Nam Soo-hyun's friend
whom he adores like his little brother."

559
00:40:26,980 --> 00:40:28,210
That's what I'll be.

560
00:40:35,290 --> 00:40:36,660
Hey, come on.

561
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:42,600
Hey, let's go for another drink.

562
00:40:44,360 --> 00:40:45,900
Today's the only day I'm available.

563
00:40:45,990 --> 00:40:47,970
You always say you're not available.

564
00:40:48,050 --> 00:40:50,830
-Are you a politician or something?
-Politics sure is important.

565
00:40:52,980 --> 00:40:55,530
Professor Song will have my back soon.

566
00:40:55,750 --> 00:40:57,780
What? Why?

567
00:40:58,350 --> 00:41:01,690
-And you've got my back.
-That's right.

568
00:41:01,780 --> 00:41:03,630
-You little...
-You too.

569
00:41:03,630 --> 00:41:04,860
[Nam Soo-hyun]

570
00:41:04,110 --> 00:41:05,960
-Come on.
-Do you want me to have your back too?

571
00:41:06,230 --> 00:41:08,210
Oh, did you dial my number by mistake?

572
00:41:09,480 --> 00:41:10,980
-Let's go.
-Did I call him?

573
00:41:11,070 --> 00:41:13,130
[Do you want to have dinner?]

574
00:41:14,370 --> 00:41:15,950
Sorry? What?

575
00:41:17,710 --> 00:41:19,820
[Do you want to have dinner?]

576
00:41:34,650 --> 00:41:35,840
[I'm curious.]

577
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:39,750
[Do you really hate me that much?]

578
00:41:39,840 --> 00:41:41,870
[Yes. Don't follow me.]

579
00:41:42,610 --> 00:41:44,200
[I don't have time to waste with you.]

580
00:41:44,290 --> 00:41:46,970
-Can I call you again?
-No, don't.

581
00:41:47,280 --> 00:41:48,820
[You might call me first, you know.]

582
00:41:49,390 --> 00:41:50,710
[That won't ever happen.]

583
00:41:52,730 --> 00:41:54,670
It's for the coffee. Bye.

584
00:42:14,950 --> 00:42:16,360
[I want to cross the line.]

585
00:42:17,110 --> 00:42:18,960
I'm not curious about you at all.

586
00:42:21,160 --> 00:42:22,740
[So don't be curious about me.]

587
00:42:23,670 --> 00:42:24,770
[Do I]

588
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:28,370
[have the right
to be curious about someone?]

589
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:47,290
-What is this?
-I already paid for it. Eat up.

590
00:42:47,950 --> 00:42:50,020
So, you were asking
if I wanted to have dinner alone,

591
00:42:50,290 --> 00:42:51,830
not with you?

592
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:53,190
Excuse me.

593
00:42:56,230 --> 00:42:57,460
Yes, do you need something?

594
00:42:57,590 --> 00:43:00,630
How am I supposed to eat this?
Look, there's a bug here.

595
00:43:00,850 --> 00:43:04,060
I'm sorry. I'll let the chef know
and get you a new one...

596
00:43:04,150 --> 00:43:07,180
And I asked for butter earlier.
When will I get it?

597
00:43:07,270 --> 00:43:09,650
I'm sorry. I'll bring it right out.

598
00:43:11,410 --> 00:43:12,510
Come here.

599
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:15,450
What did you do wrong?

600
00:43:15,540 --> 00:43:18,050
Oh, he asked for butter earlier.

601
00:43:18,140 --> 00:43:20,650
Then you should've taken care of it
right away.

602
00:43:20,730 --> 00:43:22,190
-I'm sorry.
-Do you want to get fired?

603
00:43:22,270 --> 00:43:24,520
No, I'll be careful and work harder.

604
00:43:27,070 --> 00:43:29,450
This is your final warning.
I'll be watching you.

605
00:43:29,930 --> 00:43:31,070
I'm sorry.

606
00:43:31,780 --> 00:43:33,450
And why are you always late?

607
00:43:33,540 --> 00:43:35,960
-You need to get here on time.
-I'm sorry.

608
00:43:36,050 --> 00:43:37,320
Gosh.

609
00:43:39,830 --> 00:43:40,930
Did I keep you waiting long?

610
00:43:41,850 --> 00:43:45,150
Don't come close. I smell like food.

611
00:43:50,480 --> 00:43:52,320
Why did you call me here?

612
00:43:54,390 --> 00:43:57,030
I think I know why,
but I want to make sure.

613
00:43:58,000 --> 00:44:00,290
How was the food? Did you like it?

614
00:44:00,420 --> 00:44:01,780
Don't act all sweet.

615
00:44:02,620 --> 00:44:03,720
Why did you call me here?

616
00:44:03,810 --> 00:44:05,660
So I could buy you dinner, okay?

617
00:44:05,740 --> 00:44:08,740
Did you want to make me understand
why you're such a jerk to me?

618
00:44:14,150 --> 00:44:17,930
Whenever I open my wallet,
I'm reminded of yours.

619
00:44:19,380 --> 00:44:21,450
When I see your place, I think of mine.

620
00:44:22,550 --> 00:44:25,900
I feel like I could walk out of my job
and go for drinks

621
00:44:26,950 --> 00:44:28,800
or just chill at a cafe somewhere.

622
00:44:30,470 --> 00:44:33,070
I think to myself, "It seems so easy.
Why can't I do that?"

623
00:44:36,240 --> 00:44:37,340
You see,

624
00:44:39,050 --> 00:44:41,340
I'm fine with not being able
to do stuff like that.

625
00:44:44,070 --> 00:44:46,660
But I think of my brother
whenever I see you, and it hurts me.

626
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:50,930
You could've kept it short.

627
00:44:51,900 --> 00:44:54,450
You're basically saying
you can't stand seeing me around.

628
00:44:58,500 --> 00:45:00,960
"Don't be curious about me
or try to befriend me."

629
00:45:01,490 --> 00:45:03,470
Did you call me here so I'd just get lost?

630
00:45:05,450 --> 00:45:08,050
Yes, so you'd see my situation
and come to your senses.

631
00:45:08,140 --> 00:45:10,950
I had no idea. I was all excited
on my way here, like an idiot.

632
00:45:11,440 --> 00:45:13,680
Why not pick a better place
if you wanted me to experience

633
00:45:13,770 --> 00:45:15,040
what it's like to be poor?

634
00:45:15,480 --> 00:45:16,850
This place is too boring.

635
00:45:19,140 --> 00:45:21,070
Did you have to work this hard

636
00:45:21,820 --> 00:45:23,050
to pay me back?

637
00:45:23,580 --> 00:45:24,550
I gave up my place.

638
00:45:24,640 --> 00:45:27,360
Oh, you did?

639
00:45:27,940 --> 00:45:29,210
Just to pay me back?

640
00:45:30,140 --> 00:45:32,120
So I'd leave you alone and get lost?

641
00:45:34,400 --> 00:45:37,480
Here, this is what I make in a day.

642
00:45:38,320 --> 00:45:40,390
It's less than how much your dinner costs.

643
00:45:42,940 --> 00:45:44,220
So what?

644
00:45:48,090 --> 00:45:50,550
When I pestered my dad in tears
to buy me a game console

645
00:45:50,950 --> 00:45:52,880
and asked him why my family was so poor,

646
00:45:54,470 --> 00:45:55,880
he didn't say anything.

647
00:45:56,890 --> 00:45:59,440
Then he quietly showed me
how much our total debt was,

648
00:45:59,530 --> 00:46:00,850
his salary, our living expenses,

649
00:46:02,610 --> 00:46:04,410
and the cost of raising me.

650
00:46:06,480 --> 00:46:08,680
He thought that was a faster way
to make me understand.

651
00:46:09,870 --> 00:46:10,920
You and I

652
00:46:12,460 --> 00:46:15,980
can't be friends.
There's no need for us to be friends.

653
00:46:19,860 --> 00:46:21,040
I heard you loud and clear.

654
00:46:21,880 --> 00:46:23,990
You always mean what you say.

655
00:46:24,430 --> 00:46:26,980
I prefer this rather than
being left with hope.

656
00:46:27,340 --> 00:46:29,100
Thanks for the expensive dinner.

657
00:48:27,590 --> 00:48:33,750
[Sauna]

658
00:49:11,100 --> 00:49:12,200
Jun!

659
00:49:12,820 --> 00:49:15,640
Choose your side.

660
00:49:21,050 --> 00:49:22,900
Good luck, you two.

661
00:49:30,900 --> 00:49:32,050
Hey, Jun.

662
00:49:33,190 --> 00:49:35,610
I'll join you. Where else would I go?

663
00:49:35,700 --> 00:49:37,770
I knew you'd join us!

664
00:49:38,160 --> 00:49:40,140
Don't tell me you were torn.

665
00:49:40,230 --> 00:49:41,420
That hurts my feelings.

666
00:49:41,510 --> 00:49:44,150
I almost doubted you
and thought you were ditching us.

667
00:49:45,120 --> 00:49:46,390
Let's go.

668
00:50:01,220 --> 00:50:02,540
Jun, let's eat at your place.

669
00:50:02,890 --> 00:50:06,630
-Gosh, you...
-My mom's there now.

670
00:50:06,720 --> 00:50:09,890
-She can join us.
-Yes, let's go to your place.

671
00:50:12,220 --> 00:50:13,670
Where do I begin?

672
00:50:20,360 --> 00:50:22,730
Nam Soo-hyun works part-time
at the cafeteria.

673
00:50:22,820 --> 00:50:25,290
The cafeteria?
What happened to his backer?

674
00:50:25,770 --> 00:50:26,910
Let's go there and...

675
00:50:27,000 --> 00:50:28,060
Hey.

676
00:50:29,600 --> 00:50:31,750
What we did at the convenience store
is enough.

677
00:50:32,410 --> 00:50:35,010
Let's not do the same thing again.
It's too childish.

678
00:50:35,410 --> 00:50:37,470
Jun, let's do the assignment
at your place.

679
00:50:37,560 --> 00:50:40,160
-Great idea, for a change.
-Right?

680
00:50:42,800 --> 00:50:43,900
Jun.

681
00:50:46,850 --> 00:50:49,130
-Yes.
-Let's do the assignment at your place.

682
00:50:50,670 --> 00:50:53,310
My mother is supposed to come by that day.

683
00:50:53,620 --> 00:50:54,630
Your mother?

684
00:50:54,720 --> 00:50:56,880
This is my first time hearing you
talk about your mom.

685
00:50:58,900 --> 00:51:01,010
Did we mention what day it'd be?

686
00:51:02,290 --> 00:51:05,190
-I'm hungry.
-Let's go have some tteokbokki.

687
00:51:05,280 --> 00:51:06,650
You know I don't eat tteokbokki.

688
00:51:06,730 --> 00:51:08,190
[-I'm safe here.]
-I love tteokbokki.

689
00:51:08,270 --> 00:51:09,200
Actually, I like it too.

690
00:51:09,290 --> 00:51:11,440
[-No one's curious about me,]
-I can eat it all day.

691
00:51:11,570 --> 00:51:12,630
Do you want to join us?

692
00:51:12,720 --> 00:51:14,260
[and I'm not curious about them.]

693
00:51:14,350 --> 00:51:16,410
-The tteokbokki place over there is good.
-No, thanks.

694
00:51:16,500 --> 00:51:17,510
[No pain.]

695
00:51:17,730 --> 00:51:18,880
Hey, you talk to her.

696
00:51:18,970 --> 00:51:20,640
[-And no joy.]
-Let's go.

697
00:51:20,990 --> 00:51:22,270
You're allergic to rice cakes.

698
00:51:22,350 --> 00:51:25,350
[-I'm safe here.]
-I'll take my allergy meds.

699
00:51:25,830 --> 00:51:27,110
You guys go ahead.

700
00:51:29,130 --> 00:51:35,290
[Department of Business Administration,
Professor Song Soo-kyung]

701
00:51:39,950 --> 00:51:41,580
Can I ask you something?

702
00:51:42,150 --> 00:51:44,400
You probably know the answer.

703
00:51:46,290 --> 00:51:50,160
I want to ask someone about something

704
00:51:51,750 --> 00:51:53,020
but can't muster up the courage.

705
00:51:53,110 --> 00:51:55,090
Will you gain something
by asking this question?

706
00:51:57,730 --> 00:51:59,230
Think about that first.

707
00:52:09,040 --> 00:52:11,460
I know I can't get the truth
just by asking,

708
00:52:11,900 --> 00:52:14,360
but it'll at least make
the other person think.

709
00:52:15,370 --> 00:52:18,890
And they'll either choose to
tell the truth, lie or stay silent.

710
00:52:20,480 --> 00:52:22,550
Whether you find out the truth

711
00:52:22,630 --> 00:52:25,490
or realize the other person
is lying to you

712
00:52:27,690 --> 00:52:29,810
won't it be better than doing nothing?

713
00:52:50,270 --> 00:52:51,540
What do you want to know?

714
00:52:52,510 --> 00:52:54,090
I want to know

715
00:52:56,340 --> 00:52:57,570
why I was fired.

716
00:52:58,580 --> 00:53:00,470
You got fired for a reason.

717
00:53:01,350 --> 00:53:02,540
Why do you want to know?

718
00:53:04,040 --> 00:53:06,500
I don't want to hate myself.

719
00:53:08,530 --> 00:53:09,760
Even if I do,

720
00:53:11,210 --> 00:53:14,290
I want to know which part
I have to hate and fix.

721
00:53:17,500 --> 00:53:19,220
I didn't like you from the start.

722
00:53:20,540 --> 00:53:23,350
I hate people who are incompetent, greedy

723
00:53:23,440 --> 00:53:25,600
and who just use other people.

724
00:53:26,920 --> 00:53:28,770
When I decided you were incompetent,

725
00:53:28,850 --> 00:53:31,320
that's all I saw.

726
00:53:32,810 --> 00:53:34,750
Then that'll be a huge stress for you too.

727
00:53:35,320 --> 00:53:37,480
All I'm going to do is point out
how incompetent you are.

728
00:53:41,920 --> 00:53:44,690
-But you...
-I'm sorry if I was rude.

729
00:53:46,450 --> 00:53:48,040
And thank you for your answer.

730
00:54:02,950 --> 00:54:05,680
[Myungil University]

731
00:54:05,770 --> 00:54:07,970
[2020 Second-half Sales Report:
Mijin Foods]

732
00:54:12,810 --> 00:54:14,830
-This...
-Yeo Jun gave it to me.

733
00:54:18,930 --> 00:54:20,470
So he gave this to you

734
00:54:22,140 --> 00:54:23,590
and sat over there.

735
00:54:25,040 --> 00:54:26,140
So...

736
00:54:29,530 --> 00:54:31,380
he had a change of heart.

737
00:54:31,470 --> 00:54:32,790
I have to get to work.

738
00:54:33,800 --> 00:54:35,210
Let's just do what we talked about.

739
00:54:36,350 --> 00:54:37,360
Okay.

740
00:54:42,030 --> 00:54:44,840
Maybe we should get
new members for our group?

741
00:54:47,830 --> 00:54:49,950
Give me lots of meat
and I don't want any onions.

742
00:54:50,250 --> 00:54:51,570
I'm allergic to onions.

743
00:54:55,400 --> 00:54:56,900
Are you ignoring a customer's needs?

744
00:54:56,990 --> 00:54:59,360
He just doesn't care.

745
00:54:59,450 --> 00:55:01,470
He doesn't care if you die
after eating the onions.

746
00:55:02,570 --> 00:55:03,850
Are you here to see me?

747
00:55:04,380 --> 00:55:06,050
You must be busy working

748
00:55:06,530 --> 00:55:08,120
so we'll take care of the team project

749
00:55:08,210 --> 00:55:10,270
and give you credit. No need to thank us.

750
00:55:11,460 --> 00:55:13,310
I'm doing my team project with So-bin

751
00:55:13,790 --> 00:55:15,030
and we're not giving you credit.

752
00:55:18,630 --> 00:55:20,880
Do what you want.
We'll see who wins in the end.

753
00:55:21,630 --> 00:55:24,620
Chun-guk, where's Jun?

754
00:55:25,100 --> 00:55:28,140
Oh, Jun is afraid of Soo-hyun.

755
00:55:28,450 --> 00:55:31,350
-He keeps stealing money from Jun.
-Oh, I see.

756
00:55:31,440 --> 00:55:34,650
He's stealing money from his juniors.

757
00:55:35,180 --> 00:55:36,980
That makes me feel
so ashamed as your senior.

758
00:55:37,730 --> 00:55:40,240
Is he a loan shark?

759
00:55:40,330 --> 00:55:42,790
He lends him money and makes him
pay it back with hefty interest.

760
00:55:43,190 --> 00:55:45,030
Does he have double personality
or something?

761
00:55:46,570 --> 00:55:47,810
Is he a psychopath?

762
00:55:47,890 --> 00:55:50,270
-Why you little...
-Don't you have a brain?

763
00:55:53,220 --> 00:55:55,640
-What?
-I was wondering if you ever use it.

764
00:55:58,630 --> 00:56:00,170
Or it may just be there for decoration.

765
00:56:01,180 --> 00:56:03,030
Why you little...

766
00:56:03,380 --> 00:56:05,230
No, I can't take it anymore.

767
00:56:05,320 --> 00:56:08,400
Hey, you. Come over here!

768
00:56:08,490 --> 00:56:10,510
-That's enough.
-You want a piece of me?

769
00:56:17,990 --> 00:56:19,400
[You didn't go home, right?]

770
00:56:17,990 --> 00:56:23,000
[Park Hye-ji]

771
00:56:19,660 --> 00:56:22,120
[We're at the school cafeteria. Hurry up.]

772
00:56:23,090 --> 00:56:29,430
[Jung-ho, Chun-guk, Hye-ji]

773
00:56:29,520 --> 00:56:32,770
[Chun-guk]

774
00:56:29,690 --> 00:56:31,500
[UP and Jung-ho had a fight.]

775
00:56:36,820 --> 00:56:39,460
You fight with a friend while working?

776
00:56:39,550 --> 00:56:41,040
This place isn't a playground!

777
00:56:42,140 --> 00:56:44,300
-I'm so sorry.
-Pay back the money

778
00:56:44,390 --> 00:56:47,380
for the ingredients you ruined.

779
00:56:47,820 --> 00:56:50,110
You can deduct it from my pay...

780
00:56:50,200 --> 00:56:51,520
What are you talking about?

781
00:56:51,870 --> 00:56:53,540
You're fired!

782
00:56:54,070 --> 00:56:58,290
Kids today are so shameless.

783
00:56:58,560 --> 00:57:01,020
I was going to take it easy on you
since you go to school here.

784
00:57:01,550 --> 00:57:03,530
But making money is no joke.

785
00:57:03,620 --> 00:57:04,720
Gosh.

786
00:57:06,430 --> 00:57:09,030
Please! Please give me another chance.

787
00:57:09,120 --> 00:57:10,260
I'll do better.

788
00:57:10,350 --> 00:57:11,980
Let go of me.

789
00:57:12,060 --> 00:57:14,220
-Please just give me another chance.
-Let go!

790
00:57:14,310 --> 00:57:16,420
-I'll do better.
-You're fired!

791
00:57:18,000 --> 00:57:19,980
Get out of my sight!

792
00:57:22,890 --> 00:57:25,480
My gosh...

793
00:57:34,590 --> 00:57:38,330
Hey. He gave me an excuse to
fire him at the perfect timing.

794
00:57:38,820 --> 00:57:40,660
Yes. I fired him.

795
00:57:41,760 --> 00:57:43,520
He wanted me to let him sleep
in the lounge,

796
00:57:43,610 --> 00:57:45,370
but I really didn't want to.

797
00:57:46,250 --> 00:57:48,980
Why didn't you tell me beforehand?

798
00:57:49,600 --> 00:57:51,660
It's not that hard to hire a student.

799
00:57:52,060 --> 00:57:53,250
Hold on.

800
00:57:56,590 --> 00:57:57,780
Nevermind.

801
00:58:38,220 --> 00:58:39,320
Yeo Jun!

802
00:58:42,310 --> 00:58:43,540
When did you get here?

803
00:58:53,040 --> 00:58:55,820
Oh, I guess the group meeting ended.

804
00:59:00,000 --> 00:59:01,140
I shouldn't have

805
00:59:03,250 --> 00:59:04,920
called you there.

806
00:59:07,260 --> 00:59:08,360
I'm sorry.

807
00:59:16,360 --> 00:59:18,260
Why? I had a nice meal.

808
00:59:19,970 --> 00:59:21,290
I pitied you.

809
00:59:24,590 --> 00:59:25,910
I saw how anxious you were.

810
00:59:31,410 --> 00:59:34,230
I think I was relieved.
Life was fair after all.

811
00:59:35,060 --> 00:59:37,400
Just because you're unhappy
doesn't mean I'm happy.

812
00:59:39,160 --> 00:59:40,390
I was wrong.

813
00:59:44,920 --> 00:59:46,770
You don't even have a place to go to

814
00:59:46,860 --> 00:59:48,260
and you're pitying me?

815
00:59:48,920 --> 00:59:50,290
Don't be so arrogant.

816
00:59:52,880 --> 00:59:54,640
I was so ignorant.

817
00:59:56,400 --> 00:59:59,350
Then again, we need to be on the same
level to have an actual conversation.

818
01:00:00,410 --> 01:00:02,170
I was curious,

819
01:00:02,740 --> 01:00:03,930
but it isn't fun.

820
01:00:04,850 --> 01:00:06,080
I don't want to do it anymore.

821
01:00:09,210 --> 01:00:10,840
Habits are hard to fix.

822
01:00:12,420 --> 01:00:14,840
People live the way they used to.

823
01:00:15,850 --> 01:00:17,390
Even if you try to change, you go back

824
01:00:17,480 --> 01:00:19,150
to the place your mind
and heart remembers.

825
01:00:20,820 --> 01:00:21,920
It's the same for me.

826
01:00:23,160 --> 01:00:24,870
No matter how hard I try, I go back.

827
01:00:27,120 --> 01:00:29,270
-What are you talking about?
-I know you don't mean it.

828
01:00:29,360 --> 01:00:30,940
What do you know?

829
01:00:37,060 --> 01:00:39,700
Just get over yourself and go away.

830
01:00:51,050 --> 01:00:54,570
[I'm afraid to leave my safe zone.]

831
01:00:55,890 --> 01:00:58,400
[I'm scared.]

832
01:01:37,120 --> 01:01:39,760
[At a Distance, Spring is Green]

833
01:01:40,070 --> 01:01:41,870
-Hey...
-Not interested.

834
01:01:41,960 --> 01:01:44,340
You didn't have to do a good job
or be of help.

835
01:01:44,950 --> 01:01:47,280
-At least you kept your promise.
-I won't be fooled.

836
01:01:47,370 --> 01:01:49,480
[I have a question for them.]

837
01:01:49,790 --> 01:01:51,160
[Nam Soo-hyun, stay where you are.]

838
01:01:51,240 --> 01:01:53,270
[Kim So-bin, come up front
and give us your answer.]

839
01:01:53,580 --> 01:01:56,080
What did you say? I can't hear you!

840
01:01:56,700 --> 01:01:58,020
[I'm so sorry.]

841
01:01:58,460 --> 01:02:00,790
[I know we were fine
when we didn't know each other,]

842
01:02:00,880 --> 01:02:02,550
[but I don't want to
go back to that life.]

843
01:02:02,730 --> 01:02:04,180
Don't push it.

844
01:02:04,270 --> 01:02:05,850
And if I do?

845
01:02:05,940 --> 01:02:07,170
Prepare yourself.

846
01:02:07,700 --> 01:02:09,420
[I won't stop once I start.]

847
01:02:09,500 --> 01:02:12,010
[A composite sketch.
I'm looking for someone.]

848
01:02:12,850 --> 01:02:14,960
[-Don't you remember me?
-Enjoy.]

849
01:02:16,150 --> 01:02:17,950
[I'm not going to be
friends with you anymore.]

850
01:02:18,040 --> 01:02:19,010
-Give me five.
-Yes!

851
01:02:19,450 --> 01:02:20,640
My gosh.

852
01:02:20,720 --> 01:02:24,020
[I made a friend
for the first time in my life.]


